initial commit: explorer + indexer
next.js block explorer for the asentum L1, with a sibling sqlite-backed
indexer service that powers per-address transaction history.

features:
- live homepage with block counter, network stats, recent blocks + txs
- /blocks paginated list
- /block/[number-or-hash] detail with txs + prev/next
- /tx/[hash] detail with receipt, status, gas, logs
- /address/[address] detail with balance, code detect, indexed tx history
- /validators active set with bonded stake
- universal search (block / tx / address)

indexer:
- backfill + tail loop, batched json-rpc, idempotent upserts
- sqlite via better-sqlite3, atomic per-block writes
- http api on 127.0.0.1:3002 (health / address stats / address txs)
- proxied via next.js /api/indexer/* so the explorer can stay same-origin

deployment notes for the hetzner box are in the readme.
